The following lists events that happened during '''[[1944]] in the [[Albania|People's Republic of Albania]]'''.
==Incumbents== *[[President of Albania|President]]: [[Mehdi Frashëri]], ''[[List of heads of state of Albania#German Occupation (1943–1944)|Chairman of the High Council]]'' (until 28 November), [[Omer Nishani]], ''[[List of heads of state of Albania#Communist Albania (1944–1991)|Chairman of the Presidium]]'' (starting 26 May) *[[Prime Minister of Albania|Prime Minister]]: [[Rexhep Bej Mitrovica]] (until 18 July), [[Fiqri Dine]] (18 July - 29 August), [[Ibrahim Biçakçiu]] (29 August - 28 November), [[Enver Hoxha]] (starting 22 October)
==Events== ;January * The [[National Liberation Movement (Albania)|National Liberation Movement]], supplied with British weapons, gained control of southern Albania.<ref name="countrystudies"/> ;May * The [[Party of Labour of Albania|Communists]] met to organize an Albanian government and appointed [[Enver Hoxha|Hoxha]] chairman of the executive committee and supreme commander of the National Liberation Movement.<ref name="bbc">[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/country_profiles/1004984.stm Albania timeline] BBC, A chronology of key events: 1944, news.bbc.co.uk</ref> ;October * Communists establish provisional government with [[Enver Hoxha|Hoxha]] as [[List of Prime Ministers of Albania|Prime Minister]].<ref name="countrystudies">{{cite web |url= http://countrystudies.us/albania/4.htm |title= Albania:Chronology of Important Events |website=countrystudies.us |publisher= Country Studies |access-date= 15 October 2015|quote= }}</ref> ;November * The Communists entered the capital in the wake of a German withdrawal.<ref name="bbc" /> ;December * Communist provisional government adopts laws allowing state regulation of commercial enterprises, foreign and domestic trade.<ref name="countrystudies"/>
==Births== * 12 January - [[Fatos Kongoli]], writer * 17 August - [[Rexhep Meidani]], politician, former President of Albania * 6 September - [[Skënder Hyka]], footballer * 15 October - [[Sali Berisha]], cardiologist and politician, former President and Prime minister of Albania
==Deaths== * 23 January - [[Rauf Fico]], diplomat and politician * February - [[Fuat Dibra]], politician * 1 February - [[Vasil Shanto]], one of the founders of the [[Albanian Communist Party]] * 5 March - [[Ismail Ndroqi]], politician and philosopher * 7 August - [[Skënder Muço]], lawyer and leader of [[Balli Kombëtar]] * September - [[Llazar Fundo]], communist, later social-democratic journalist and writer
