The '''''Annales Sangallenses maiores''''' (Latin for ''Greater Annals of St Gall'') are [[annals]] compiled in [[St Gallen]], covering the years 927 through to 1059.<ref>[http://www.geschichtsquellen.de/repOpus_00406.html Geschichtsquellen]</ref> They continue the ''[[Annales Alamannici]]'', the St Gallen version of which reaches up to 926.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bsbdmgh.bsb.lrz-muenchen.de/de/fs1/object/goToPage/bsb00000868.html?pageNo=72&sortIndex=010:050:0001:010:00:00 |title=MGH. Scriptores (in Folio) (SS). Band 1: Annales et chronica aevi Carolini: Annales Sangallenses, Augienses et Weingartensis }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>


