The '''Chamalals''' are an indigenous people of [[Dagestan]], [[Russia]] living in a few villages in the [[Tsumadinsky District]] on the left bank of the [[Andi-Koisu river]]. They have their own language, [[Chamalal language|Chamalal]], and primarily follow [[Sunni Islam]], which reached the Chamalal people around the 8th or 9th century. There are about 5,000 ethnic Chamalals (1999, Kubrik).<ref name=Ethnologue>[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=cji Ethnologue report for Chamalal]</ref> They are culturally similar to the [[Avar people (Caucasus)|Avars]].

Neighboring peoples are the [[Godoberi people|Godoberi]], Avars, [[Bagvalal people|Bagvalals]], and [[Tindi people|Tindis]].

