{{Infobox Union |name= FTUK/FPRK |country= [[Kazakhstan]] |affiliation= [[GCTU]] |members= 1.5 million |full_name= Federation of Trade Unions of the Republic of Kazakhstan |native_name= |image= [[File:FTUK logo.png]] |founded= |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Astana]], Kazakhstan |people= [[Siyazbek Mukashev]], chairman |website= [http://www.fprk.kz www.fprk.kz] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Federation of Trade Unions of the Republic of Kazakhstan''' (FTUK) is a [[national trade union center]] in [[Kazakhstan]]. It has a membership of 1.5 million, and is the successor organization to the official trade unions of the communist era.
FTUK is affiliated with the [[General Confederation of Trade Unions]].
