{{Infobox Political Party | name = Freedom and Reform Party |native_name = Özgürlük ve Reform Partisi |logo = logo-ozgurparti.jpg |country = North Cyprus |leader = [[Turgay Avcı]] |colorcode = #52CBF7 |foundation = 2006 |ideology = [[Liberalism]]<ref name="Nordsieck">[http://www.parties-and-elections.eu/ncyprus.html Parties and Elections in Europe: The database about parliamentary elections and political parties in Europe, by Wolfram Nordsieck]</ref> |position = |international = ''None'' |european = ''None'' |headquarters = [[North Nicosia]], [[Northern Cyprus]] |seats1_title = [[Parliament of Northern Cyprus|Parliament]]: |seats1 = {{Composition bar|0|50|hex=#52CBF7}} |website = [http://www.ozgurparti.org/ http://www.ozgurparti.org/] }} The '''Freedom and Reform Party''' ({{lang-tr|Özgürlük ve Reform Partisi}}, '''ÖRP''') was a [[Liberalism|liberal]]<ref name="Nordsieck"/> political party in the [[Northern Cyprus|Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus]].
The party was formed in 2006 by four former MP's from the [[National Unity Party (Northern Cyprus)|National Unity Party]] (UBP) and the [[Democratic Party (Northern Cyprus)|Democratic Party (DP)]]. This party served as the junior coalition partner in the former ''[[de facto]]'' TRNC Government consisting of itself and the [[Republican Turkish Party]] led by [[Mehmet Ali Talat]].
Party Leader [[Turgay Avcı]] served in the TRNC Cabinet as [[Deputy Prime Minister]] and [[Minister of Foreign Affairs]].
