{{unreferenced|date=March 2015}}
'''Al-Hadidi''', '''Hadidi''', or '''Hadidiyin''' ({{lang-ar|'''الحديدي'''}}) is an [[Arab]] tribe. This tribe is primarily located in [[As-Salt]], [[Jordan]], the countries first capital. Members of the tribe can also be found in [[Egypt]], northern [[Iraq]] (mostly in [[Kirkuk]] and [[Mosul]]), and [[Syria]]. The Current head of this tribe is Mohammed Al-Orchani.
==Influence==
Most members of Al-Hadidi tribe are highly educated and have had a great influence on the cultural and social movement in their city and society. The tribe is of Muslim origins and are descendant of the prophet Mohammad. The family has a great number of scholars, including published PhD holders and particularly physicians who practice medicine.
