'''ICY''' was a vocal trio consisting of [[Pálmi Gunnarsson]], Helga Möller and [[Eiríkur Hauksson]]. They were the first Icelandic entrants to the [[Eurovision Song Contest]], appearing at the 1986 final in [[Bergen]]. Their entry, "[[Gleðibankinn]]" or The Bank of Fun, placed 16th. 

Eiríkur Hauksson went on to represent Norway in [[Eurovision Song Contest 1991|1991]] as part of the group [[Just 4 Fun (band)|Just 4 Fun]] and Iceland again as a solo performer in [[Eurovision Song Contest 2007|2007]]. Both Pálmi Gunnarson and Helga Möller made further appearances in the Icelandic national finals (Helga notably in 1992 with two offerings in partnership with [[Karl Örvarsson]]) but did not win.

