{{Infobox mountain | name = Le Parrain | photo = Le Parrain et al.jpg | photo_caption = Le Parrain (left) and [[Le Pleureur]] (centre) from the west side | elevation_m = 3259 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 115 | prominence_ref = <ref>Retrieved from the [[Swisstopo]] topographic maps. The key col is the Col du Crêt (3,144 m).</ref> | parent_peak = [[La Ruinette]] | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | location = [[Valais]], [[Switzerland]] | range = [[Pennine Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|46|02|44.5|N|7|21|5.2|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Le Parrain''' is a [[mountain]] of the Swiss [[Pennine Alps]], located east of [[Fionnay]] in the canton of [[Valais]]. Its summit (3,259 m) lies within the valley of [[Bagnes]] but near the watershed with the valley of [[Val d'Hérens|Hérens]].
"Le Parrain" is a common name for designating the [[Godparent|godfather]] in [[French language|French]], hence the mountain's name is in English "The Godfather".
