{{Politics of the Republic of the Congo}}
'''Parliamentary elections''' were held in the [[Republic of the Congo]] on 2 May 1993, with a second round in several constituencies on 6 June. The result was a victory for the Presidential Tendency coalition, which won 65 of the 125 seats in the [[National Assembly of the Republic of the Congo|National Assembly]].<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/cg.html Elections in Congo-Brazzaville] African Elections Database</ref>
