:''This is an article about Sibylla of Burgundy, queen of Jerusalem. For her namesake, see [[Sibylla of Burgundy, Duchess of Burgundy]].''
[[File:Roger2 Sibyla.jpg|thumb|right|Sibylla with her husband.]]
'''Sibylla of Burgundy''' (1126 – 16 September 1150 in [[Salerno]]) was the second [[queen consort]] of [[Roger II of Sicily]].{{sfn|Houben|2002|p=96}}

She was a daughter of [[Hugh II, Duke of Burgundy]], and his wife Felicia-Matilda of Mayenne.{{sfn|Houben|2002|p=96}}

In 1150, Sibylla married King [[Roger II of Sicily]]. On 29 August of that year, Sibylla gave birth to a stillborn child and died of complications of the childbirth.{{sfn|Houben|2002|p=96}} She was buried in the church of the Monastery of [[La Trinità della Cava|La Trinità]] [[Cava de' Tirreni]].

